<!DOCTYPE showme.pack
  SYSTEM "../Symbols.dtd">
<showme.pack xmlns="Compositor"
             xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
             id="Exa_AlternatingSeriesConverges"
             xsi:schemaLocation="Compositor file:/C:/xampp/htdocs/moodle/mod/msm/NewSchemas/Compositor.xsd">
	  <texsupport xmlns="" href="../Analysis_TeXSupport.xml"/>
	  <title>Alternating Series Test: Example.</title>
	  <showme>
		    <statement.showme>
			      <para xmlns="">
            <para.body>Determine the convergence behavior of the series</para.body>
         </para>
			      <math.display xmlns="">
				        <latex>\sum_{n=1}^{\infty} \dfrac{\cos(n\pi)}{ \sqrt[4]{n^3} }</latex>
			      </math.display>
		    </statement.showme>
		    <answer.showme xmlns="">
         <answer.showme.block>
            <answer.showme.block.body>
			            <para>
                  <para.body>First we observe that</para.body>
               </para>
			            <math.array column="3">
                  <row rowspan="1">
                     <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle">
                        <math>
                           <latex>\cos(n\pi)</latex>
                        </math>
                     </cell>
                     <cell colspan="1" halign="center" valign="middle">
                        <math>
                           <latex>=</latex>
                        </math>
                     </cell>
                     <cell colspan="2" halign="center" valign="middle">
                        <math>
                           <latex>(-1)^n</latex>
                        </math>
                     </cell>
                  </row>
               </math.array>
			            <para>
                  <para.body>for all <math>
                        <latex>n\in \NNr</latex>
                     </math>. Next we observe that the numbers <math>
                        <latex>a_n := 1/\sqrt[4]{n^3}</latex>
                     </math> are all positive. So the given series is an alternating series. If the sequence <math>
                        <latex>(a_n)</latex>
                     </math> is strictly decreasing and converges to <math>
                        <latex>0</latex>
                     </math>, we may apply the alternating series test and conclude that the given series converges to a number <math>
                        <latex>\leq a_0 = 1</latex>
                     </math>.</para.body>
               </para>
			            <para>
                  <para.body>So we analyze the sequence <math>
                        <latex>(a_n)</latex>
                     </math>:</para.body>
               </para>
			            <ol>
				              <li>
                     <para>
                        <para.body>The sequence <math>
                              <latex>(n^3)</latex>
                           </math> is strictly increasing and converges to <math>
                              <latex>+\infty</latex>
                           </math>.</para.body>
                     </para>
                  </li>
				              <li>
                     <para>
                        <para.body>So the sequence <math>
                              <latex>\sqrt[4]{n^3}</latex>
                           </math> is strictly increasing and converges to <math>
                              <latex>+\infty</latex>
                           </math>.</para.body>
                     </para>
                  </li>
				              <li>
                     <para>
                        <para.body>So the sequence <math>
                              <latex>a_n=1/\sqrt[4]{n^3}</latex>
                           </math> is strictly decreasing and converges to <math>
                              <latex>0</latex>
                           </math>.</para.body>
                     </para>
                  </li>
			            </ol>
			            <para>
                  <para.body>Thus the alternating series test applies to the given series, and we see that it converges to a number <math>
                        <latex>\leq a_0=1</latex>
                     </math>.</para.body>
               </para>
		          </answer.showme.block.body>
         </answer.showme.block>
      </answer.showme>
	  </showme>
</showme.pack>
